'''Intimacy''' is the degree to which a person can share feelings with another in a [[Intimate relationship|relationship]]. Intimacy is occasionally linked with [[Sexual intercourse|sex]] but it can also occur in a [[Platonic love|nonsexual]] or unromantic relationship. The [[dialectic]]s of connection-autonomy and openness-closedness manipulate the communication of intimacy between partners.

